  %section
    %h2 Like typing commands on tryruby.org
    :markdown
      Except instead of Ruby code, you'll be executing _shell script_.  I know
      that sounds crazy but don't worry!

      <small>This is how computers used to work, before Apple popularized
      [graphics][gui].</small>

        [gui]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphical_user_interface

      Just type each of these lines (don't copy & paste; you'll learn better!),
      hitting "enter" after each:

          $ cd <the folder with your website>
          $ git init
          $ git add .
          $ git commit -m "First commit"

