  %section
    %h2 Commit Yr Changes!
    :markdown
      I know, I know, you've much more you want to do. CSS takes forever. But
      let's commit your changes now. Hold Alt (Command on a Mac) and hit Tab
      to get back to Terminal/Git-Bash. Then do this:

          $ git add .
          $ git commit -m "Workin' on CSS, w00t w00t"

  %section
    %h2 What the git?
    :markdown
      Open up the [Git GUI][gitx] that you downloaded. It'll ask you to open a
      folder. Open the folder that your website is in.

      [![Try Git][badge]][try-git]

      _Preeeeeetty sweeeet_, right? You never need to worry about screwing
      anything up! Just _commit often_.

        [gitx]: http://git-scm.com/downloads/guis
        [badge]: assets/images/try-git.png
        [try-git]: http://www.codeschool.com/courses/try-git

      <small>Git does **waaaay** more than that. Be excited! We'll learn more in
      week 4.</small>

